        <p>Richard Rand letter praises PayPal online payment system (June 29 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I have been an eBayer for about a year, primarily for clothing, and I have been rarely burned. I also signed on to PayPal (''Easy Payments Put Hole in the Pocketbook,'' Online Shopper, June 29).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I have been an eBayer for about a year, primarily for clothing, and I have been rarely burned. I also signed on to PayPal (''Easy Payments Put Hole in the Pocketbook,'' Online Shopper, June 29).</p>
        <p>I agree that it makes it easy to spend more, but it also expedites the transaction. Sending a check from Hawaii to most of the continental United States takes up to five days, so most of my transactions had taken about two weeks. With PayPal, that time has been reduced to as little as five days.</p>
        <p>RICHARD RAND  Honolulu</p>
      </block>
